# ğŸ“ Definition of Ready (DoR)

A story is ready when:

- [ ] Has a clear description
- [ ] Has acceptance criteria
- [ ] Has mapped dependencies
- [ ] Has a defined impact and objective
- [ ] Is small enough to fit in a sprint
- [ ] The team understands what needs to be done

# âœ… Definition of Done (DoD)

A story is complete when:

- [ ] Meets all acceptance criteria
- [ ] Has been tested
- [ ] Has no known bugs
- [ ] Has been reviewed by the team
- [ ] Is integrated into the environment
- [ ] Is documented when necessary

